  <content type="html"><![CDATA[ <blockquote><p>This is a simple example of using <strong>oj.Table</strong>, with static data.</p></blockquote>

<hr />




<p>
If you need a simple table in your application try out <span style="text-decoration :underline;"> <a title ="oj.Table" href="http://www.oracle.com/webfolder/technetwork/jet/uiComponents-table-sortableTable.html"> oj.Table.</a></span>  In this example, the table is using an simple array but you have other options like a Knockout.js array or an Oracle JET Collection (<a title ="oj.Collection" href="http://www.oracle.com/webfolder/technetwork/jet/uiComponents-table-ojCollectionTable.html"> oj.Collection</a>).
</p>




<hr />




<h3 id="smallimage">Oracle JET - oj.Table with static data</h3>




<p>Using static data is a great place to start</p>




<div class="full zoomable">
   <img src="../static/img/ojtable-simple.png" alt="oj.Table - Simple" />
</div>




<hr />




<h2 id="preformattedtext">Sorting</h2>




<p>By default, all of the columns have sort enabled.  We can make a couple of quick changes so that only one of the colmns can be sorted.</p>




<p>First, disable sorting for the table by setting the sortable attribute <code>columnsDefault: {sortable: 'disabled'}</code>, then add the sortable attribute to the specific column you want to sort <code>sortable: 'enabled'</code>. Here is a look at the code for the table with sort enabled for the id column.</p>


<p><figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span> <span class="nt">id</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;table&quot;</span> <span class="nt">summary</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;Department List&quot;</span> <span class="nt">aria-label</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;Departments Table&quot;</span>
       <span class="nt">data-bind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;ojComponent: {component: &#39;ojTable&#39;, </span>
<span class="s2">                                data: datasource, </span>
<span class="s2">                                columnsDefault: {sortable: &#39;disabled&#39;}, </span>
<span class="s2">                                columns: [{headerText: &#39;Id&#39;, </span>
<span class="s2">                                           field: &#39;DeptId&#39;,</span>
<span class="s2">                                           sortable: &#39;enabled&#39;},</span>
<span class="s2">                                          {headerText: &#39;Name&#39;, </span>
<span class="s2">                                           field: &#39;DeptName&#39;},</span>
<span class="s2">                                          {headerText: &#39;Location Id&#39;, </span>
<span class="s2">                                           field: &#39;LocationId&#39;},</span>
<span class="s2">                                          ]}&quot;</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
<span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="o">&gt;</span></code></pre></figure></p>

